OL,5,C'damp squib' funding row
OL,6, Catch-up plans worth #1.4bn for school
OL,7, pupils in England have been accused of
OL,8, being a "damp squib" by head teachers.
OL,10,FThe funding will mostly be spent on
OL,11,Ftutoring sessions to make up for
OL,12,Flearning lost in the pandemic.
OL,14,FBut the plans are much more limited
OL,15,Fthan the #13.5bn which the Education
OL,16,FPolicy Institute (EPI) had calculated
OL,17,Fwould be required.
OL,19,FPrime Minister Boris Johnson said: "We
OL,20,Fwill do everything we can to support
OL,21,Fchildren who have fallen behind."
